<event name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER" unique="true">
	<text>You're hailed by a Mantis vessel. "You not know how hard repair with claw is. Teleporter is broken, can you fix? We will pay you, as we are so kind."</text> 
	<ship load="SHIP_MANTIS_FIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Agree to help repair their teleporter.</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="doors" lvl="2">
		<text>(Upg. Doors) Agree, but lock your doors tight in case of a trap.</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_DOORS"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="REPAIR">
		<text>(Repair Drone) Dispatch the repair drone to fix it. [-1|]</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_REPAIR"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="BOMB_HEAL_SYSTEM">
		<text>(Repair Burst) Use the bomb to fix the teleporter. [-1}]</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_BOMB"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>We can't help.</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_NO"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES">
	<event>
		<text>As you dock your ship with the Mantis, they immediately come charging through your doors! Their ship turns hostile, and you should prepare for a fight.</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<boarders min="2" max="2" class="mantis"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Their teleporter does indeed appear to be in critical condition. It doesn't take long to fix it, and the Mantis pay you as promised.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_DOORS">
	<event>
		<text>As you dock your ship with the Mantis, they immediately come charging for your doors. Luckily they aren't able to break their way through, but you still have to deal with their ship.</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis do not seem to be attempting to trick you, and their teleporter does indeed appear to be in critical condition. It doesn't take long to fix it, and the Mantis pay you as promised.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_REPAIR">
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis are surprised to see a drone instead of crew, and it doesn't take long for them to reveal their hostile intentions. They cut up the drone and their ship turns hostile.</text>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="drones" min="-1" max="-1"/>
		</item_modify>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis's teleporter does indeed appear to be in critical condition. It doesn't take long for the drone to fix it, and the Mantis pay you as promised.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="drones" min="-1" max="-1"/>
		</item_modify>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_YES_BOMB">
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis are surprised to see your burst weapon targeting their ship. Whether they always had hostile intentions or think your repair burst is a real weapon is irrelevant, because the Mantis have turned hostile.</text>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="missiles" min="-1" max="-1"/>
		</item_modify>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis's teleporter does indeed appear to be in critical condition. Your bomb promptly fixes it, and the Mantis pay you as promised.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
		<item_modify>
			<item type="missiles" min="-1" max="-1"/>
		</item_modify>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="MANTIS_BROKEN_TELEPORTER_NO">
	<event>
		<text>"Fine. Tell truth, we lie. Now, we take supplies from you and make even better teleporter!"</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Mantis don't attempt to push further.</text>
		<choice>
			<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
			<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Do nothing.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="MANTIS_PIRATE_FAKE"> <!--NEW! Multiverse-->
	<text>A Mantis pirate ship defends this beacon, claiming to be one of the Hive's enforcers. They demand you pay them either scrap or a slave, or be obliterated.</text> 
	<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_MANTIS" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Refuse.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You make it clear to the pirate that you have no interest in giving them anything but death. You both hurry to prepare for battle.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Pay their fee.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Mantis seem satisfied and fly away, leaving you to grumble over your lost scrap.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="-25" max="-35"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" blue="false" lvl="1">
		<text>Hand over a slave.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Mantis come aboard and pick one of your crew to take back with them. Your crew struggles, trying to free themselves, but the last you see of them is screaming, being dragged out of the ship.</text>
			<removeCrew>
				<clone>false</clone>
				<text>Tempting as it is to clone your crew, you made the decision to give them up, and you aren't going to break Federation code for it.</text>
			</removeCrew>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" blue="false" lvl="0" max_lvl="0">
		<text>The on-board AI recommends terminating these pirates with extreme prejudice.</text>
		<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="MANTIS_SLUG_TAUNT" unique="true"> <!--NEW! Multiverse-->
	<text>A Slug and Mantis ship appear to be squaring off at this beacon, but weapons have not yet been fired. Both ships simultaneously hail you. The Slug speaks first, "Federation, how fortuitousss that sssomeone elssse who I'm ssssure will apprecccciate the humor of thessse feeble pea-brained Mantisss and their pitiful attemptsss at dialect!" The Mantis cuts them off, "You stupid ones! Listen, how you drag out s's. True sign of inferiority." Both ships eagerly await your input on the situation.</text> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Agree that the Slugs are superior.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Slug points at the Mantis and laughs, but is cut off when the Mantis becomes enraged and powers up its weapons and attacks!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_MANTIS_TAUNT" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Agree that the Mantis are superior.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Slug grumbles as the Mantis gloats. Furious at your shot at their ego, the Slug activates its weapon barrels towards you!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_SLUG_TAUNT" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Can't you both just get along?</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Mantis and Slug glance at each other for a solid minute before they both simultaneously say "nahhhh", and fly straight towards each other, weapons blazing. You fly away before you get caught up in the fighting.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="MANTIS_SLUG_TAUNT_MANTIS_WIN">   
	<text>The Slug cackles, his already massively inflated ego having been expanded once again. Though he clearly still thinks of you as inferior, he gives you some additional fuel along with the remains of the Mantis ship.</text>
	<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
	<item_modify>
		<item type="fuel" min="4" max="6"/>
	</item_modify>
</event>
<event name="MANTIS_SLUG_TAUNT_SLUG_WIN">   
	<text>The Mantis lets out a cry of victory, and performs a strange ritual dance. They leave you with the remains of the Slug ship and fly away.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
</event>

