		<text>We have both Kaz and Lai, we can do this.</text>
		<event>
			<text>As you start to approach the palace, a Bishop guard stops you. "You cannot be here! You will regret stepping so close to her majesty's palace!"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Have Lai talk it out with the guard.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"So you carry two traitors, yet you still wish to gain access to Hive? I would kill you on spot, but the Queen has heard of dishonorable KazaaakplethKilik's arrival and wishes to see him..."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue into the palace.</text>
						<event>
							<text>You're ceremoniously 'welcomed' into the palace, and with some brief fanfare Leikonpliiinakra emerges, dressed in golden robes. By the way you see Kazaaak looking at her, she must be quite desirable for a Mantis. She pays little attention to you or Lai, instead flirting with the Mantis warrior by your side. After some exchanged formalities, she walks back into the palace and you are ushered to follow.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Follow.</text>
								<event>
									<text>The next location you find yourself in is a long dining hall, its tables decorated in Mantis cuisine. At last, Leikonpliiinakra speaks to your group as a whole, and strangely well spoken for a Mantis at that. "As soon as I heard my darling Kaz had returned, I knew you would come here. Sit, and feast as much as you like. We will discuss whatever business you have come here for after."</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event>
											<text>You spend most of the feast in awkward silence, with only occasional conversation between Kazaaak and Leik. Eventually, things turn more serious. "I am not oblivious to Kaz's recent movements in Coalition space, but I have chosen to turn a blind eye to them. I can only expect that you have come here to negotiate the Hive's withdrawal from the alliance."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Yes.</text>
												<event>
													<text>"Then I'm afraid that I both cannot do such a thing nor would it have any impact. Even if I were to withdraw from the Coalition, which frankly is an idea I would not entirely be opposed to, you would have to convince the Leikonpliiinakra of every reality to withdraw as well. You might not realize it, but the Coalition has secured many realities of its own. But regardless of this, the Hive is not in a position to cut ties with the Coalition. After the Federation-Mantis War our economy has been in ruin, and the industrial might of the Kleptocracy and Theocracy have aided us greatly."</text>
													<choice hidden="true">
														<text>Oh...</text>
														<event>
															<text>With that conclusion made, Leik turns back to Kazaaak. "My apologies dear, but in your absence the Hive has not grown fond of you. But traveling in-arms with another traitor to the Episcopacy and a Federation Captain has not helped your image. I love you, but my role as queen means I must place the safety of the Hive first. It is clear where your line in the sand has been drawn, so this must mark the end of us. And I'm afraid there is another reason I have allowed you here: the capture of the fugitive you have brought with you, Laiiikarkapi. I apologize my dear, for it was my fault appointing you to this role. But such things cannot go unpunished. This is the last stop for all of you. I can at least promise you your funerals will be held with honor." Leikonpliiinakra stands up, and her guards draw their weapons. You hurry out of the palace just in time to witness a massive cruiser approaching to stop you! Seems it's time to fight your way out of here.</text>
															<ship load="SHIP_BISHOP_BOSS" hostile="true"/>
															<choice hidden="true">
																<text>Continue...</text>
																<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
															</choice>
														</event>
													</choice>
												</event>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>We can't do this.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You are not prepared for this mission. Better to turn back now than risk going any further.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
